  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HP 05 - Principles and Neglected Crises</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved understanding and application of the Fundamental Principles in difficult contexts to ultimately increase safe humanitarian access for vulnerable populations. Our work on the Fundamental Principles has three levels: - To examine the application of the Fundamental Principles in today s humanitarian situations and analyse the distinctive role of the Movement in different contexts (Case studies); - To strengthen and support Movement understanding and application of the principles including promotion of the FPs and sharing of innovative approaches to dilemmas (Movement Initiative); and - To promote greater understanding and acceptance of the distinctiveness of the Red Cross and the relevance of humanitarian principles with policy makers and aid actors globally and in the UK (Global level engagement).</narrative>
  </description>
